article.headline: Dartmouth 45, Princeton 44
article.story: PRINCETON, N.J. (AP) -- Alex Barnett scored 23 points as Dartmouth held off Princeton 45-44 on Saturday night. Dartmouth (8-12, 3-4 in Ivy League) snapped a 19-game losing streak in Princeton with the win, while the Tigers (10-10, 1-5) -- playing without injured forward Edwin Buffmire and leading scorer Kyle Koncz -- lost for the sixth time in seven games. Noah Savage led Princeton with 12 points and three assists. The teams traded baskets for most of the game until the Big Green took the lead for good on Jonathan Ball's free throw with 2:24 left, which made the score 41-40. The lead grew when Ball scored on a putback with 1:20 left, but Princeton cut the deficit to 43-42 on Michael Strittmatter's layup with 54 seconds remaining. DeVon Mosley eventually sealed the win for Dartmouth by making two free throws with 19.2 seconds left. Savage then missed a 3-point attempt that would have tied the game, but Luke Owings got the rebound and scored with just one second left. Dartmouth then ran out the clock to earn the victory. The Big Green committed 15 turnovers, but made 46.2 percent of their shots and outrebounded the Tigers 31-20.
